cs.DS, cs.SI, cs.DB, cs.LG, cs.CC

Reasoning: 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is the most likely category as the paper deals with developing an algorithm for graph summarization. 
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is also likely as the paper mentions social networks as an example of real-world graphs. 
- cs.DB (Databases) is another possible category as the paper discusses the challenges of processing and performing analytics on large graphs. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is a possible category as the paper proposes a novel weighted sampling scheme to sample vertices for merging. 
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is another possible category as the paper provides analytical bounds on the running time of the algorithm and proves approximation guarantee for the score computation.
